&lt;h2 id=&quot;assumption&quot;&gt;Assumption:&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;\{X_1, X_2,\dots X_n\}$ are identical independent distribution random variables with uniform distribution: $\mu = E(X) = \frac{a + b}{2}$ and variance: $\sigma^2 =E(X^2) =\frac{(b-a)^2}{12}&lt;/script&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;consider-the-random-variable&quot;&gt;Consider the random variable:&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;$Z_n = \frac{X_1 + X_2 + \dots + X_n -n\mu}{\sqrt{n\sigma^2}}= \sum_{i=1}^{n}\frac{X_i -\mu}{\sqrt{n\sigma^2}}= \sum_{i=1}^{n}\bar{X_i}$&lt;/p&gt;

